{"title": "Swift handover gives Singapore\u2019s incoming PM more time to make his mark", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-04-19", "content": "After a protracted succession plan that spanned over five years, lots of speculation with other names thrown into the ring, and the delays caused by a pandemic, the final phase of appointing a new prime minister will take just 30 days.\nOn April 15, Prime Minister Lee Hsien Loong said he would hand over the reins of government to current Deputy Prime Minister Lawrence Wong on May 15."}